      {
        "id": 2200885,
        "name": "Merrill Lindquist",
        "username": "Merrill_Lindquist",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/merrill_lindquist/{size}/884_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-06-14T15:46:43.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I posted on it while it was happening\u2026over on the Weather Thread. The hail we had here in Calistoga was the size of petite pois - just the size of my newly set berries. No damage. I saw photos in one of the news reads that showed damage from walnut sized hail, and they were saying which vineyards were reporting damage. I am very fortunate.</p>",
