      {
        "id": 2201146,
        "name": "Merrill Lindquist",
        "username": "Merrill_Lindquist",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/merrill_lindquist/{size}/884_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-06-14T20:37:04.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Lee Braem\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Lee Braem:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Merrill, I didn\u2019t know there was weather thread. I don\u2019t see it in the Index. Glad your vines ok.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>It is in the Cellar Rats section. All things growing and vintage related.</p>\n<p>Hail the size of walnuts was reported - mine were more like spitballs.</p>\n<p>I said my fruit was ok, but I went out again and took a very close look. No damage. However, now that we have suckered and shoot thinned, and the fruit is set, I am starting to see more variation from cluster to cluster. To my eye right now, I am not seeing a huge crop for this vintage. Time will tell.</p>",
